@NODE HISTORIA

History:

0.1 - First version.
0.2 - First public version
0.3 - Removed some bugs.
      Localization and Polish locale added.
      Added CDB2 and CDB3 options to send low level commands.
      Added checking that command is send to CD-ROM/CD-R/CD-RW and DVD (last
     one is still untetsted). WolnyCD cannot be accidentally used as
     "WolnyHD" :-).
      Added messages about errors and return code.
0.4 - Added show info about device
	Little optimize
0.5 - Added TEAC/JVC SCSI CD-R speed settings
0.6 - Removed Enforcer hits
0.7 - Added experimental UPDATE option
0.8 - Added START and STOP options
      Optimized program code
      Added support for any speed rate for all ATAPI and SCSI drives 
     (excluding CD-R TEAC SCSI and compatible)
0.9 - Added EJECT, LOAD, PREVENT and ALLOW options
1.0 - Added support for tooltypes
      Added native MorphOS version
      Removed CDB2 and CDB3 options, in that place added easier in usage 
     SPEEDRATE option
      Modified main code
      Added new options - TEST and STATUS
      Changed default device to scsi.device, default option to STATUS
      Added WINDOW tooltype
      Changed some locale strings
      Added new option - XCAL
      Changed STOP option
      Changed INQUIRY for ATA HDD (MORPHOS)
1.1 - Added TOSHIBA/S option for Toshiba SCSI drivers
1.2 - Added VOLUME/K option - use volume (ie. FoundationDC:) or drive 
     (ie. CD0:) name
      Added Italian catalog
@ENDNODE
